"The intervention consisted of a web-based microlearning platform designed to support academic speaking through segmented learning units (bite-sized modules). The platform was developed using Moodle with custom plugins to support audio recording and self-reflection features. Each module focused on a specific speaking function (e.g., explaining concepts, structuring arguments, responding to questions) and followed a consistent instructional sequence:\n\n1. **Concept exposure (5-7 minutes):** Students engaged with short multimedia input, including video explanations, infographics, and annotated examples.\n2. **Explain-to-learn task (10-15 minutes):** Students explained the concept orally using their own words, recording their explanation via the platform (Feynman technique).\n3. **Metacognitive reflection (5 minutes):** Students responded to structured prompts encouraging planning (before speaking), monitoring (during explanation), and evaluation (after performance)."
